### QA1 — SMOKE TEST
### Event Passport PWA — Template
### Run this first to confirm the API is reachable before running other suites.
### Docs: https://github.com/your-org/event-passport-pwa

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# CONFIGURATION
# Update these variables before running.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@eventId = <your-event-id>

# Production example:
# @baseUrl = https://your-app.up.railway.app/api


# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# S01 — API is online
# Expected: 200 + active event object
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
### S01
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/active

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# S02 — Sponsors load
# Expected: 200 + sponsor list
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
### S02
GET {{baseUrl}}/sponsors?eventId={{eventId}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# S03 — Admin login endpoint responds
# Expected: 401 (wrong credentials intentional — confirms endpoint is alive)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
### S03
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "smoke@test.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}


### LOGIN TEST
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}